<topic xml:lang="en-us" id="gui-virtualboxmanager">
  <title><ph conkeyref="vbox-conkeyref-phrases/vbox-mgr"/></title>
  
  <body>
    <p><ph conkeyref="vbox-conkeyref-phrases/vbox-mgr"/> is the user interface for <ph
        conkeyref="vbox-conkeyref-phrases/product-name"/>. You can use <ph conkeyref="vbox-conkeyref-phrases/vbox-mgr"/>
      to create, configure, and manage your virtual machines. </p>
    <p>This section describes the main features of the <ph conkeyref="vbox-conkeyref-phrases/vbox-mgr"/> user interface.
      Subsequent sections and chapters describe how to use <ph conkeyref="vbox-conkeyref-phrases/vbox-mgr"/> to perform
      tasks in <ph conkeyref="vbox-conkeyref-phrases/product-name"/>. </p>
    <p>When you start <ph conkeyref="vbox-conkeyref-phrases/product-name"/>, the <b outputclass="bold"><ph
          conkeyref="vbox-conkeyref-phrases/vbox-mgr"/></b> window is displayed. </p>
    <p><xref href="#gui-virtualboxmanager/fig-vbox-manager-initial"/> shows <ph conkeyref="vbox-conkeyref-phrases/vbox-mgr"/> the
      first time you start <ph conkeyref="vbox-conkeyref-phrases/product-name"/>, before you have created any
      virtual machines.
    </p>
